He was 22.

43:19.597 --> 43:21.838
<i>$0 young.</i>

43:21.900 --> 43:25.109
<i>I don't think
I could bear that.</i>

43:25.169 --> 43:28.309
The only thing you can do
is just remind yourself

43:28.373 --> 43:30.216
that the pain
isn't real.

43:33.645 --> 43:36.489
<i>Mimi spent time in a
monastery where she was taught</i>

43:36.547 --> 43:40.256
<i>that all pain and suffering
are illusions.</i>

43:40.318 --> 43:43.788
Isn't that right, Mimi?

43:43.855 --> 43:45.163
Yes.

43:47.759 --> 43:52.936
Mimi, do you believe this pain
you're feeling now is real?

43:52.997 --> 43:54.271
No.

43:54.332 --> 43:56.608
Isn't real.

43:56.668 --> 44:00.707
But you feel it.

44:00.772 --> 44:05.221
Only because I haven't
achieved enlightenment yet.

44:05.276 --> 44:11.022
<i>Mimi, I am Jesus,</i>

44:11.082 --> 44:13.153
and I'll never tell you
that you're not hurting

44:13.217 --> 44:15.788
when you really are.

44:15.853 --> 44:20.825
I don't deny your pain,
and I'll never ignore it.

44:23.528 --> 44:28.238
I think it's better
if pain is just an illusion

44:28.299 --> 44:31.405
because if I thought what
I was feeling was real,

44:31.469 --> 44:34.211
I would kill myself.

44:34.272 --> 44:37.276
<i>Hey, baby, you don't have
to live like this, you know?</i>

44:37.341 --> 44:40.345
You can always
go back to rehab.

44:40.411 --> 44:43.756
Maybe she needs
a reason to face reality.

44:43.815 --> 44:46.762
What do you know?

44:46.818 --> 44:49.128
I know pain.

44:49.187 --> 44:51.861
It breaks my heart.

44:51.923 --> 44:56.565
<i>My hope for humankind was never
pain, suffering, and death.</i>

45:00.464 --> 45:03.741
<i>It's Kamal, your supplier.</i>

45:03.801 --> 45:07.749
<i>He's running late
because of the storm.</i>

45:07.805 --> 45:10.843
Oh, and don't worry
about the storm.

45:10.908 --> 45:13.889
<i>It's going to hit further
north along the coast.</i>

45:15.980 --> 45:17.960
This is him.

45:24.422 --> 45:26.402
Will you still
be here today?

45:29.527 --> 45:31.507
<i>Couple hours?</i>

45:36.133 --> 45:38.875
I can't wait a couple hours.
I'm dying.

45:38.936 --> 45:40.381
Look, I know you’re
hurting, baby.

45:40.438 --> 45:43.612
Look-listen to me, you're
halfway through detox now.

45:43.674 --> 45:46.416
If we stay the course
we can start again.

45:46.477 --> 45:50.653
We can start again clean.

45:50.715 --> 45:52.023
I'm gonna die!

45:52.083 --> 45:54.063
You're not going to die!

46:07.198 --> 46:10.645
What's wrong, Mimi?

46:10.701 --> 46:15.013
He doesn't understand
how badly I hurt.

46:15.072 --> 46:17.985
<i>That's too bad because
if he doesn't understand</i>

46:18.042 --> 46:19.612
the depth of your pain,

46:19.677 --> 46:25.059
he'll never appreciate
the height of your victory.

46:25.116 --> 46:28.620
What is victory?

46:28.686 --> 46:30.859
<i>Your triumph over drugs.</i>

46:30.922 --> 46:34.836
And more importantly,
finally finding the peace

46:34.892 --> 46:40.843
<i>and the security that you've
sought after your whole life.</i>

46:40.898 --> 46:43.879
Can I tell them
about your life?

46:46.404 --> 46:50.477
Mimi was born
in a tiny village.

46:50.541 --> 46:52.145
You could say
that even from birth

46:52.210 --> 46:55.214
she was a victim
of the drug trade.

46:55.279 --> 46:57.190
<i>Her father worked
in the poppy fields</i>

46:57.248 --> 47:01.924
<i>while her mother worked
in the processing plants.</i>

47:01.986 --> 47:04.626
They had no choice.

47:04.689 --> 47:06.828
We were so poor.

47:06.891 --> 47:12.739
You either worked the fields
or you starved.

47:12.797 --> 47:17.769
But-
they were good people.

47:17.835 --> 47:20.372
They loved me.

47:20.438 --> 47:23.817
They send me to school
at the monastery

47:23.874 --> 47:27.151
<i>so I would have
a better life.</i>

47:27.211 --> 47:28.849
<i>You loved it there.</i>

47:28.913 --> 47:30.586
<i>Yes.</i>

47:30.648 --> 47:32.628
<i>It's wonderful.</i>

47:38.356 --> 47:40.495
<i>What happened?</i>

47:40.558 --> 47:42.936
<i>Mimi's father
was wrongly accused</i>

47:42.994 --> 47:46.840
by the drug lord
of stealing.

47:46.898 --> 47:52.871
<i>The only payment
he would accept was Mimi.</i>

47:55.606 --> 47:57.244
They dragged her out
of the monastery

47:57.308 --> 47:59.686
and sold her to
a Bangkok brothel.

47:59.744 --> 48:02.691
<i>Don't tell them
about it, please.</i>

48:02.747 --> 48:05.887
<i>I won't.</i>

48:05.950 --> 48:07.930
<i>We skip to Bruno?</i>

48:10.922 --> 48:14.631
<i>For Bruno, it was
love at first sight.</i>

49:36.073 --> 49:39.646
<i>He couldn't bear
to see you working there,</i>

49:39.710 --> 49:44.716
<i>so he bought you
from the gangster.</i>

49:58.863 --> 50:04.313
At first I wasn't sure
what he was going to do.

50:04.368 --> 50:09.613
Whether he would
be like the others.

50:09.673 --> 50:12.620
I belong to him.

50:12.676 --> 50:18.490
He can use me, beat me,
put me on the street,

50:18.549 --> 50:23.726
but instead he freed me.

50:23.788 --> 50:25.927
<i>And the drugs?</i>

50:25.990 --> 50:31.463
<i>Dealers usually hook their
women so they can control ‘em.</i>

50:31.529 --> 50:34.510
Isn't that right, Bruno?

50:36.567 --> 50:41.107
Another word out of you,
I put a bullet in your head.

50:41.172 --> 50:43.152
<i>It's about time.</i>

50:44.775 --> 50:50.817
<i>Bruno wasn't to blame,</i>

50:50.881 --> 50:52.292
not directly anyway.

50:52.349 --> 50:55.860
Call it insecurity.

50:55.920 --> 51:01.893
Bruno, Mimi never quite felt
comfortable around your friends.

51:04.762 --> 51:08.335
They all look at me
like I was some dumb Bai girl.

51:08.399 --> 51:13.144
When Bruno wasn't around,
then they talk about my accent,

51:13.204 --> 51:18.950
the way I dress,
the way I walk, everything.

51:19.010 --> 51:22.287
<i>You thought you'd be happy
if you were as sophisticated</i>

51:22.346 --> 51:27.694
and worldly as they were.

51:27.752 --> 51:30.631
<i>So when your friend Louise
invited you to do heroin</i>

51:30.688 --> 51:34.101
<i>with her,
you couldn't say no.</i>

51:34.158 --> 51:37.662
<i>You told yourself you couldn't
get hooked the first time,</i>

51:37.728 --> 51:41.608
<i>especially if you
snorted it.</i>

51:41.665 --> 51:46.114
<i>Louise was so smart
and so happy,</i>

51:46.170 --> 51:48.150
<i>maybe you'd be too.</i>

51:53.877 --> 51:56.084
<i>But it didn't last.</i>

51:56.147 --> 52:01.096
That hole in your heart,
it remains.

52:01.151 --> 52:03.825
Stop romanticizing it.

52:03.887 --> 52:06.868
<i>You think that helps?</i>

52:06.924 --> 52:09.871
She's not an addict
because of some deep

52:09.927 --> 52:14.706
phycological
or spiritual need.

52:14.765 --> 52:17.302
She's an addict
because she used heroin.

52:17.368 --> 52:19.507
It's that simple.

52:19.570 --> 52:22.346
It's an addictive drug,
and once you start using it,

52:22.406 --> 52:24.852
you can't stop.

52:24.909 --> 52:27.947
That's why it's a
multibillion-dollar business.

52:28.012 --> 52:30.117
<i>Why did she take
it in the ?rst place?</i>

52:30.180 --> 52:33.218
Did you ever ask her?

52:33.284 --> 52:34.957
Are you blaming me?

52:35.019 --> 52:36.521
Do you blame yourself?

52:36.587 --> 52:37.861
No.

52:37.922 --> 52:40.334
That's good.

52:40.391 --> 52:44.567
Because even if Mimi
had never met you,

52:44.628 --> 52:47.165
<i>despair would have eventually
driven her to drugs.</i>

52:47.231 --> 52:50.235
<i>Her environment
was so corrupt.</i>

52:50.301 --> 52:53.282
Did you know
Ric was a twin?

52:55.306 --> 52:56.717
You mean
there's two of them?

52:56.774 --> 52:59.687
Was.

52:59.743 --> 53:04.692
<i>She died when
they were just 18.</i>

53:04.748 --> 53:06.091
<i>She?</i>

53:06.150 --> 53:10.064
He's got a chick twin?

