I guess his parents forgot
which one to put the dress on.

53:16.760 --> 53:23.234
And Bruno, if he has his way,
he's going to kill you.

53:38.849 --> 53:44.925
<i>Is that true, Ricky boy?</i>

53:44.989 --> 53:49.062
Are you gonna kill me?

53:49.126 --> 53:51.106
If there's any justice.

53:54.164 --> 54:00.137
Fortunately, Ric and I
define justice differently.

54:03.440 --> 54:08.082
It's not my will that
any of you die today.

54:08.145 --> 54:14.118
<i>I came to give you life,
life more abundantly.</i>

54:15.686 --> 54:18.428
Tell that to my son.

54:18.489 --> 54:23.461
Chris, does your
son still exist?

54:24.995 --> 54:29.637
Helen, does he?

54:29.700 --> 54:33.944
<i>That pan of you that hears
my voice knows deep inside</i>

54:34.004 --> 54:37.110
<i>that Timothy is in a much
better and more glorious place,</i>

54:37.174 --> 54:42.283
<i>and one day you'll be
reunited with him.</i>

54:42.346 --> 54:46.021
That's why Chris
despises you.

54:46.083 --> 54:48.689
<i>Your small
but lingering hope</i>

54:48.752 --> 54:53.792
<i>that one day you'll
see Timothy again.</i>

54:53.857 --> 54:56.201
<i>It's an affront to him.</i>

54:56.260 --> 54:58.672
<i>He resents you for it.</i>

54:58.729 --> 55:03.371
<i>In his eyes you traded
true pain and mourning</i>

55:03.434 --> 55:06.608
<i>for some self-comforting
religious fantasy.</i>

55:06.670 --> 55:12.985
In his eyes Timothy
just blinked away,

55:14.745 --> 55:20.991
<i>never to be again, no heaven,
no hell, no nothing.</i>

55:21.051 --> 55:25.898
But Chris, that's not a very
emotionally satisfying

55:25.956 --> 55:28.766
kind of atheism, is it?

55:28.826 --> 55:32.501
You can't rage against a void
because a void can't hear you.

55:32.563 --> 55:34.474
A void can't be hurt
or punished.

55:34.531 --> 55:35.805
You needed someone.

55:35.866 --> 55:41.782
<i>You needed something to
direct all that anger at.</i>

55:41.839 --> 55:43.512
You needed God.

55:43.574 --> 55:47.545
