that you believed</i>

55:57.921 --> 56:02.995
half of what you once
said you believed.

56:03.060 --> 56:08.840
<i>Chris once was very publicly
proud of being a man of faith.</i>

56:08.899 --> 56:11.903
<i>He could name it and claim it
with the best of them,</i>

56:11.969 --> 56:16.918
so revered as one of the
company's moral compasses.

56:16.974 --> 56:19.454
One that-

56:19.509 --> 56:23.184
Oh, Chris had no problem

56:23.247 --> 56:27.491
marketing sub-prime
mortgage packages.

56:27.551 --> 56:30.054
You knew they were bad
from the beginning.

56:30.120 --> 56:32.498
That's nonsense!
Nonsense!

56:32.556 --> 56:35.332
<i>I had plenty of them in
my own personal portfolio.</i>

56:35.392 --> 56:38.373
<i>You sold them all
for a substantial pro?t</i>

56:38.429 --> 56:40.705
before they collapsed.

56:40.764 --> 56:45.042
<i>You used the pro?t to
